0xp solo, you would get 800xp each in a duo and so on up to about 500xp each in a group of 6. So that is a 300% bonus for a group of 6. People in AO actually disliked soloing because it was such slow xp.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This seems to be the only way to improve this situation.  Verant wants to promote grouping over soloing or duoing, yet soloing will always return better XP due to the way they have set it up.<br>
<br>
Originally, a person soloing would obtain say 1000 XP for a kill.<br>
For each addional person they added to the group, they would obtain 2% more XP.<br>
This made a table that looked like this:<br>
1: 0% bonus.<br>
2: 2% bonus.<br>
3: 4% bonus.<br>
4: 6% bonus.<br>
5: 8% bonus.<br>
6: 10% bonus.<br>
<br>
This <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/editorial/011401_EQ_Producers_letter.html">was changed in Jan 2001</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> when the XP curve was adjusted so that it looked like this:<br>
1: 0% bonus.<br>
2: 2% bonus.<br>
3: 6% bonus.<br>
4: 10% bonus.<br>
5: 14% bonus.<br>
6: 20% bonus.<br>
<br>
Not a whole lot.<br>
<br>
Say you're killing a mob that returns 1000 XP.<br>
Here's how it plays out with the above table:<br>
1: 0% bonus, 1000 XP each.<br>
2: 2% bonus, 510 XP each.<br>
3: 6% bonus, 353 XP each.<br>
4: 10% bonus, 275 XP each.<br>
5: 14% bonus, 228 XP each.<br>
6: 20% bonus, 200 XP each.<br>
<br>
With the force that PoP mobs hit for, and the reduced blue con range, those that could solo low blues by melee means without support, like Rangers, Magicians, Monks, etc... have been screwed over as you're dead before you can do any real damage.  Those that don't have to come in contact with the mobs like Druids, Necros, Wizards, etc... are getting insane XP even if the kills take longer than normal.  Making a group return a noticible amount of XP more than soloing or duoing is the only way to truely make grouping desirable for all.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Umbrae:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I went from getting an cool 1% some times 2% AA solo kill to an easy 5% (PoD) to 7% (some times 8% PoV HoH) AA per solo kill. looks like they signifcantly boosted XP gain.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Exactly.  This is why a much larger bonus needs to be given to groups.  If you could join a 6 person group and gain 8% AAXP per kill, and given that the group reduces your risk of death and increases the kill rate, you wouldn't be seen soloing.  Groups would happily be filling their empty slots rather than retaining a duo, or a 4 person group to maximise XP.  As it is, your group has to kill over 6 times as fast as someone soloing to make better XP.<br>
